<a href="http://www.confectionerynews.com/On-your-radar/Cocoa-supply/ICCO-cuts-cocoa-deficit-forecast?utm_source=copyright&amp;utm_medium=OnSite&amp;utm_campaign=copyrightSOFTS-Cocoa%20rebounds%20after%20grind%20data,%20sugar%20eases" target="_self">http://www.confectionerynews.com/On-your-radar/Cocoa-supply/ICCO-cuts-co...</a></p><p>8. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Corporate Council on Africa, ‘USDA official lauds growth in African agribusiness sector’, 24 February 2011</p><p>
<a href="http://www.africacncl.org/(35aixw45ox2qmlitzahn2dar)/reader.aspx?viewmode=pressrelease&amp;content_id=78c626a8-4dd8-4aa7-8119-d3a6955ee823" target="_self">http://www.africacncl.org/(35aixw45ox2qmlitzahn2dar)/reader.aspx?viewmod...</a></p><p>9. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <i>World Watch</i>, ‘Chocolate could bring the forest back’, by C. Bright with D. Nierenberg, November/December 2001</p><p>&nbsp;
<a href="http://www.worldwatch.org/node/510" target="_self">http://www.worldwatch.org/node/510</a></p><p>10. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Nature Conservancy, ‘Papua New Guinea: Sweet success’, April 2 2012</p><p>
<a href="http://www.nature.org/ourinitiatives/regions/asiaandthepacific/papuanewguinea/explore/sweet-success.xml" target="_self">http://www.nature.org/ourinitiatives/regions/asiaandthepacific/papuanewg...</a></p><p>11.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pacific Agribusiness Research and Development Initiative (PARDI)/Australian Center for International Agricultural Research, <i>Cocoa</i><i>&nbsp;Value Chain Review, </i>November 2011</p><p>
<a href="http://www.spc.int" target="_self">www.spc.int</a></p><p><b>Other key press articles</b></p><p>1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reuters, ‘Bumper crop upsets view: Ivory Coast in decline’, 5 August 2011</p><p>
<a href="http://af.reuters.com/article/commoditiesNews/idAFL6E7J422620110805" target="_self">http://af.reuters.com/article/commoditiesNews/idAFL6E7J422620110805</a></p><p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reuters, ‘Analysis: Smuggling pads Ghana’s record cocoa harvest’, 10 May 2011</p><p>
<a href="http://af.reuters.com/article/ghanaNews/idAFLDE7441F020110510" target="_self">http://af.reuters.com/article/ghanaNews/idAFLDE7441F020110510</a></p><p>3. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BBC, ‘Chocolate boost for Sao Tome farmers’, 7 March 2011</p><p>
<a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-12261276" target="_self">http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-12261276</a></p><p>4. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <i>Jamaica</i><i>&nbsp;Gleaner</i>,<i>&nbsp;‘</i>Cocoa-crop revival: EU project to increase production’, 16 March 2011</p><p>
